{
  "texts": [
    "The slight difference is that, for the main results of JUMP++, we scale the beam size N c to 1.2 times larger than the original (N c =60), and the sampled beam size is set to the same value as the original beam size (N c ′ =50).",
    "We set the perplexity temperature T to 10 - foot_2.",
    "Time limit Setup In the defense experiments, we try different scenarios against individual attacks.",
    "For the individual attack experiments, a time limit of 300 seconds is allocated per attack case under the no-defense scenario, and 480 seconds in other defense experiments (SmoothLLM, DUMP) to account for the additional runtime required for the defense process.",
    "Adversarial Data for Training In the defense experiments, we specifically choose AutoDAN as the attacker."
  ]
}